      <tr><td class="sm">16 threads, <a href="/db/item.html?item=5690&amp;start=0">1</a>  page(s) long</td><td class="sm" align="right">&nbsp;</td></tr></table></form><a class="sm" href="/db/item.html?item=5690">Root thread</a>
<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td>
	     <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%" >
	     <form action="/cgi-bin/mrate.pl" name="f98781022747944">
	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="">Very difficult to make</a> <a id="fs8" href="#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Fri, Apr 20th 7:43 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br /><span id="notbold">Score:</span> Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>This is one of the best wisdom belts in the game. However, the difficulty of making it more than justifies its quality.<br/><br/>It appears that none of the Velious leather or fur tailored items are ever trivial. There is at least 1 tailor in the game that have a skill of 250. They have not found a trivial for any of these recipes and have confirmed that several of them are definitely not trivial at 250.<br/><br/>Each attempt to make this belt requires 2 velium tempers (28pp each), 2 small bricks of velium (dropped by a number of 30+ mobs in different velious zones), 1 drake egg (foraged in Skyshrine or dropped by named drakes in that zone) and 1 Cobalt Drake Hide (about a 1 in 5 drop from drakes in Cobalt Scar, level 40+ with AE damage and debuff attacks).</p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan="2" align="right" class="mform" id="fs8">1 Reply</td></tr>
	     </form></table>
<tr><td colspan="2"><ul>
<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td>
	     <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%" >
	     <form action="/cgi-bin/mrate.pl" name="f98783248955973">
	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=5690&amp;mid=98783248955973">RE: Very difficult to make</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=5690&amp;mid=98783248955973#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Sat, Apr 21st 1:54 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=27649"><span id="Sage">Palarran</span></a><br /><b><span id="Sage">Sage</span></b><br /><span id="notbold">119 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score:</span> Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>I have been attempting other velious leathers so far...<br/>At skill 134-135 it took me 18 attempts to make one studded arctic wyvern mask.<br/>At skill 138-139 it took me 12 attempts to make one black panther leggings.<br/><br/>Anyway, a little walkthrough on how you'd make one...<br/><br/>=== The pelts ===<br/>The cobalt drakes in cobalt scar aren't necessarily that difficult.&nbsp;&nbsp;Under all circumstances, do not let the drake melee--he has a breath proc, an AE 300 point dd + dispell.  Used to be 1000 damage but it was scaled back.  This AE breath attack has a HUGE range, comparable to Vox/Nagafen (some have said larger?!).  You will make a lot of people upset if they are on the beach and repeatedly hit by your drake's breath....The drakes must be killed by spells without letting them hit you.<br/><br/>How you'd kill them them depends on your class:<br/>If you're a druid like me, and in the upper 40's or 50's...soloing them works well.  It's tedious but it works.  Ensnare, then root/dot/meditate/repeat.  I'm a 52 druid, and it takes me about 5 minutes to kill one, and another 3 or 4 minutes to meditate the mana back to full mana (I'm left at about 60%).  Drakes are level 44 so they give decent exp.  (Edit: Bah!  They lowered the level on us, they're not 44 anymore.  They have less hp now too, but that doesn't make them a whole lot easier to hunt.)<br/>If you're a wizard, I've heard they are soloable too, probably with a similar technique.  A 56 wizard said it uses up 70% of his mana to kill one, though the fight is much shorter.  My guildmate, a 52 wizard, has been soloing them as well, though he has been killed many times in the process.<br/><br/>Other casters will want to group with someone that can snare and use a similar method.  If you can't find someone who can snare, you'll<br/>probably want to group and stand on opposite sides of the drake, trying to make it fly back and forth in the middle by alternating casting.  Being able to root it in the middle before the fight would probably help too.  This is much riskier but I've heard it can be effective once you get it down.<br/><br/>If you're a melee type...buy your pelts from others, or have guildmates hunt them for you.  I suppose if you had one person that could snare and one person that could fear, then a few tanks could try to kill the drake VERY quickly...but because of the random duration of fear this is very dangerous.  The two casters would be better off fighting the drakes on their own.<br/><br/>Note that wyverns and drakes are social--they will join the fight if you are close enough.  For me the best place to fight the drakes has been near their patrol paths, but right up against the east zone wall.<br/><br/>There are 4 drakes in the zone if I remember right.  Learn their patrol paths--one on the south side flies east/west along a line, one in the southeast corner by the dragon circle flies in a triangle pattern, and two on the east side fly north/south.  Their paths overlap a little, so make sure you catch the drake when it's somewhere in the middle of its route so another drake doesn't join in.  Staying against the zone wall should keep the wyverns from joining in, except for the wyvern on the south side--haven't found a good way to fight him yet.  Usually by the time I've killed the other three they've started to repop.<br/><br/>Being non-KOS to dragons (ClawsofVeeshan) makes hunting in cobalt scar much easier.  You can travel almost anywhere on land safely, and walk right up to the drakes and wyverns without them attacking you while you're setting up or meditating.  It makes entering cobalt scar safer too, since you can be teleported over without worrying about whether the drake in the corner will attack as soon as you zone in (which happens often).  Even though the drakes and wyverns are on ClawsofVeeshan faction, you will NOT take any faction hits from killing them unless you fight the named ones Yvolcarn and Azureake.  If you haven't killed anything on ClawsofVeeshan faction yet, expect to kill about 300 frost giants/drakkel dire wolves/etc. to get to dubious.  Should be less if you fight the Kromzek in Kael, from what I've heard...<br/><br/>Anyway...that's how you'd get the drake pelts.  They do seem to be about a 1 in 5 drop.  They are probably the second most difficult pelts to get for tailoring, the most difficult probably being haze panther hides due to haze panthers being a somewhat rare spawn (and having a similar drop rate).<br/><br/>=== The bonings ===<br/>For small bricks of velium, the easiest way to get them is to sweep through the orc miners in the crystal caverns.  A high level druid/monk combination works well.  If you're lucky you might get other loot from the crystal caverns in the process.  Keep in mind that other people want to hunt there for exp though...<br/>I've heard that Velketor's Labyrinth near the entrance is good too, and will give 40's/50's exp too.  I haven't tried it, but unless the drop rate is significantly higher there, the orc miners are better if all you're interested in is the velium.<br/><br/>Other places, according to EQ Traders' Corner(www.eqtraders.com): "various mobs in Tower of Frozen Shadow (5th floor, especially), sentries and such in Skyshrine, and various spider and golem-type creatures in other zones (Velketor's Labyrinth, underneath Icewell Keep, etc.)"<br/><br/>To make the bonings:<br/>Combine 1 file, 1 small brick of velium and 1 coldain velium temper.  The coldain velium temper is sold in the little rogue guild in Thurgadin.  If you're KOS to the dwarves, you'll have to get someone else to buy them for you--this is the only known place to get it.  Minimum cost is 26.25pp.  The bonings are light and stackable, so you'll want to convert the bricks to bonings often.  Trivial with smithing skill under 80, according to EQTraders.<br/><br/>=== The drake eggs ===<br/>This has been by far the most difficult tailoring component for me to get.  Other people have reported foraging one every half hour in Skyshrine.  Two hours of foraging there with 200 skill has gotten me nothing.<br/><br/>They are also rare drops from named wyverns in Skyshrine.  I cannot fight them because I'm trying to keep my ClawsofVeeshan faction up.  My bard will hunt them eventually...<br/><br/>Drake eggs are edible, I've been told.  Make sure you don't eat them!  Bring plenty of other food.<br/><br/>Going rate on drake eggs seems to be 50pp, from what I've read.  I have not been able to buy any yet.  Even when I offer yew leaves for trade...<br/><br/>If you do get a drake egg, combine that and a flask of water in a brew barrel to get the drake egg oil.<br/><br/>=== Putting it all together ===<br/>In a coldain tanning kit (available only in the Thurgadin bank for 10.5pp, has 8 giant slots and weighs 2) combine...<br/>* 1 cobalt drake hide<br/>* 2 velium bonings (unstacked)<br/>* 1 drake egg oil<br/>* 1 belt pattern (if you have the tailoring skill to attempt this, you know where to get it--again see EQTraders)<br/><br/>Then, if you're extremely lucky, you'll end up with your very own Cobalt Drake Belt.  Until your skill is 200+ or so, expect about a 5% success rate at any skill level.  I imagine these should sell for 10k+.  I'm not selling mine once I've made one though. :)<br/><br/>Palarran Taurina, 52 druid<br/>Bunnies of Chaos<br/>Ayonae Ro</p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
